                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1378</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Ochoa Bogh<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Article 4.7 (commencing with Section 51257) to Chapter 2 of Part 28 of Division 4 of Title 2 of the Education Code, relating to school recognition. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SB 1378, as amended, Ochoa Bogh.
                          California Excellence in Service Learning Designation Program.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"> Existing law establishes a system of public elementary and secondary schools operated and maintained by local educational agencies throughout the state. Existing law establishes the State Department of Education in state government, and vests the department with specified powers and duties relating to the state’s public school system.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the department to establish a California Excellence in Service Learning Designation Program to publicly recognize and designate<font color="#B30000"><strike> schoolsites and local educational agencies,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> schoolsites,</i></font> as defined, that meet certain requirements related to service learning, as provided. The bill would require the
			 department to develop an annual application process and adopt application criteria for the California Excellence in Service Learning Designation Program, as specified, and would require a California Excellence in Service Learning designation to be valid for 3 years, after which a schoolsite<font color="#B30000"><strike> or local educational agency</strike></font> seeking to renew its designation would be required to reapply pursuant to a renewal process and criteria determined by the department.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.856637720462963"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Article 4.7 (commencing with Section 51257) is added to Chapter 2 of Part 28 of Division 4 of Title 2 of the Education Code, to read:</div><div><div><div id="id_80D9D397-7FE6-4726-BB6B-DDBBA5B584BA"><div><h5 style="text-align:left;">
                Article
               4.7. California Excellence in Service Learning Designation Program</h5></div></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">51257.</h6> This article shall be known, and may be cited, as the California Excellence in Service Learning Designation Program.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">51257.1.</h6> For purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(a) “Applicant” means a<font color="#B30000"><strike> schoolsite or a local educational agency.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> schoolsite.</i></font></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Local educational agency” means a school district, county office of education, or charter school.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(b)</i></font> “Schoolsite” means a publicly funded school serving pupils in kindergarten or any of grades 1 to 12, inclusive.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(c)</i></font> “Service learning” means an educational approach<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> in kindergarten, including transitional kindergarten, or any of grades 1 to 12, inclusive, </i></font> that intentionally combines meaningful community service activities with instruction and reflection to
						  support pupil progress toward academic and civic engagement learning objectives while meeting societal needs.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">51257.2.</h6> (a) The department shall establish a California Excellence in Service Learning Designation Program in order to publicly recognize and designate schoolsites<font color="#B30000"><strike> and local educational agencies</strike></font> that meet certain requirements and signal which schoolsites<font color="#B30000"><strike> and local educational agencies</strike></font> demonstrate excellence in service learning.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) (1) The department shall develop an application process that provides annual opportunities for schoolsites<font color="#B30000"><strike> and local educational agencies</strike></font>
						  to earn the California Excellence in Service Learning designation by demonstrating compliance with the application criteria adopted pursuant to paragraph (2).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The department shall adopt application criteria for schoolsites<font color="#B30000"><strike> and local educational agencies</strike></font> seeking the California Excellence in Service Learning designation. The department shall consider including, as part of the application criteria, a requirement that an applicant do all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Designate a staff member to serve as a point of contact for service learning.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) Provide professional development opportunities to train staff on service
						  learning.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) Develop a dedicated web page on the applicant’s internet website with easily accessible information and resources on service learning.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) (1) Once an applicant is awarded a California Excellence in Service Learning designation, it shall display its active status designation, as identified by the department, on the applicant’s internet website.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) A California Excellence in Service Learning designation shall be valid for three years, after which an applicant seeking to renew its designation shall reapply pursuant to a renewal process and criteria determined by the department.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The department may request additional
						  information to verify if an applicant that has earned a California Excellence in Service Learning designation continues to adhere to the California Excellence in Service Learning designation criteria adopted pursuant to paragraph (2) of subdivision (b).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) (A) Notwithstanding paragraphs (1) and (2), if the department finds that an applicant that has earned a California Excellence in Service Learning designation ceases to comply with the criteria adopted pursuant to paragraph (2) of subdivision (b) during the three-year designation period, the applicant shall lose the designation.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) An applicant that loses the designation pursuant to subparagraph (A) may reapply pursuant to subdivision (b).</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
